{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/j4vm9a","slide":4,"text":"About 75 seconds. The most interesting work was in the edge cases. Creation must immediately store version one. A changed edit appends the next snapshot, but a no-op update must not create noise. Concurrent requests must not receive the same number, which is why the row lock matters. I added tests for these behaviors, as well as history retrieval, project scoping, deletion, and migration of existing data."}
